          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong></strong></p> <p> <p><b>Sunshine in the Courtroom Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill establishes a framework to allow federal court proceedings&#8212;in district courts, in circuit courts, and at the Supreme Court&#8212;to be photographed, recorded, broadcast, or televised. </p> <p>Specifically, it authorizes the presiding judge to permit media coverage of court proceedings, subject to requirements and limitations. </p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
